outpost to help

00:16:41.790 --> 00:16:45.380 align:middle line:10%
us get farther and farther into
space, to asteroids, to Mars

00:16:45.380 --> 00:16:46.480 align:middle line:10%
eventually.

00:16:46.480 --> 00:16:48.000 align:middle line:84%
I think the science
on Station is

00:16:48.000 --> 00:16:49.590 align:middle line:84%
making incredible
breakthroughs that

00:16:49.590 --> 00:16:51.720 align:middle line:84%
are going to help us make life
better for people right here

00:16:51.720 --> 00:16:52.020 align:middle line:90%
on Earth.

00:16:52.020 --> 00:16:54.394 align:middle line:10%
>>RICK MASTACCHIO: We and our
other international partner

00:16:54.394 --> 00:16:58.950 align:middle line:10%
crewmates are working off
the planet for the planet.

00:16:58.950 --> 00:17:01.620 align:middle line:10%
>>MIKE HOPKINS: NASA, along
with our international partners,

00:17:01.620 --> 00:17:04.410 align:middle line:10%
