00:17:19.170 --> 00:17:22.319 align:middle line:10%
Astronauts aboard
NASA's Orion spacecraft

00:17:22.319 --> 00:17:27.540 align:middle line:10%
will explore the asteroid and
return to earth with samples.

00:17:27.540 --> 00:17:30.870 align:middle line:10%
This experience will help
NASA test new systems

00:17:30.870 --> 00:17:35.500 align:middle line:10%
and capabilities such as solar
electric propulsion, which

00:17:35.500 --> 00:17:38.440 align:middle line:10%
will send cargo as part
of human missions to Mars.

00:17:38.440 --> 00:17:42.230 align:middle line:90%


00:17:42.230 --> 00:17:45.050 align:middle line:10%
NASA's new space
launch system will

00:17:45.050 --> 00:17:47.855 align:middle line:10%
enable these proving
ground missions

00:17:47.855 --> 00:17:50.950 align:middle line:10%
to test new capabilities.

00:17:50.950 --> 00:17:56.120 align:middle line:10%
Human missions to Mars will rely
on Orion and an evolved version

00:17:56.120 --> 00:18:02.350 align:middle line:10%
