individuals did it.

00:41:26.462 --> 00:41:28.170 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Some scientists
think that there

00:41:28.170 --> 00:41:32.790 align:middle line:84%
could have been a nuclear
holocaust, a war on Mars.

00:41:32.790 --> 00:41:35.400 align:middle line:90%
What do you think?

00:41:35.400 --> 00:41:38.310 align:middle line:84%
>>ZUBRIN: I don't think there
was a nuclear war on Mars,

00:41:38.310 --> 00:41:41.160 align:middle line:84%
because I don't think there was
a technological civilization

00:41:41.160 --> 00:41:43.990 align:middle line:90%
on Mars.

00:41:43.990 --> 00:41:46.500 align:middle line:84%
And I don't think
there's ever going

00:41:46.500 --> 00:41:48.120 align:middle line:84%
to be a nuclear
war on Mars, even

00:41:48.120 --> 00:41:50.730 align:middle line:84%
though I think there will be
a technological civilization

00:41:50.730 --> 00:41:51.660 align:middle line:90%
on Mars.

00:41:51.660 --> 00:41:52.530 align:middle line:90%
Because I think--

00:41:52.530 --> 00:41:53.970 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It will be us.

00:41:53.970 --> 00:41:56.760 align:middle line:84%
>>ZUBRIN: Well, I think
as humanity matures,

00:41:56.760 --> 00:41:59.160 align:middle line:84%
we go out to space,
what we're going

00:41:59.160 --> 00:42:03.090 align:middle line:84%
to do by going out into
space is prove that there are

00:42:03.090 --> 00:42:04.980 align:middle line:84%
infinite number of
resources, that there

00:42:04.980 --> 00:42:06.990 align:middle line:90%
is no need to have wars.

00:42:06.990 --> 00:42:11.510 align:middle line:84%
Because it is people
that are resourceful.

00:42:11.510 --> 00:42:13.790 align:middle line:84%
And if we can turn Mars
into a living world

00:42:13.790 --> 00:42:17.210 align:middle line:84%
we can turn innumerable
worlds into living worlds.

00:42:17.210 --> 00:42:20.700 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: If we go to Mars
for any length of time,

00:42:20.700 --> 00:42:21.650 align:middle line:90%
what will we do there?

00:42:21.650 --> 00:42:24.050 align:middle line:90%
What will we build?

00:42:24.050 --> 00:42:26.060 align:middle line:84%
>>ZUBRIN: Well, if we
go to Mars to settle,

00:42:26.060 --> 00:42:29.540 align:middle line:84%
the first thing we
need to do is learn

00:42:29.540 --> 00:42:32.780 align:middle line:84%
how to take Martian
materials and turn them

00:42:32.780 --> 00:42:35.831 align:middle line:90%
into resources, OK.

00:42:35.831 --> 00:42:37.580 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Including the
water that's there.

00:42:37.580 --> 00:42:38.380 align:middle line:90%
>>ZUBRIN: Yes.

00:42:38.380 --> 00:42:41.900 align:middle line:84%
See look, there really
is no such thing

00:42:41.900 --> 00:42:43.910 align:middle line:90%
as a natural resource.

00:42:43.910 --> 00:42:46.190 align:middle line:84%
There's only natural
raw materials.

00:42:46.190 --> 00:42:51.020 align:middle line:84%
Land was not a resource until
people learned how to farm.

00:42:51.020 --> 00:42:54.620 align:middle line:84%
It is farming that turns
to land from simply space

00:42:54.620 --> 00:42:58.130 align:middle line:84%
that you have to travel over
into a resource in itself.

00:42:58.130 --> 00:42:58.930 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Right.

00:42:58.930 --> 00:43:01.680 align:middle line:84%
>>ZUBRIN: OK, petroleum
was underground,

00:43:01.680 --> 00:43:04.910 align:middle line:84%
