until people go there,

00:43:20.270 --> 00:43:23.330 align:middle line:84%
because it is people
who are resourceful.

00:43:23.330 --> 00:43:26.450 align:middle line:84%
And now we go there, we'll
learn how to extract water

00:43:26.450 --> 00:43:28.157 align:middle line:90%
from the Martian surface.

00:43:28.157 --> 00:43:29.990 align:middle line:84%
We'll learn how to
extract geothermal energy

00:43:29.990 --> 00:43:31.790 align:middle line:90%
from the Martian subsurface.

00:43:31.790 --> 00:43:33.920 align:middle line:84%
We'll learn how to
grow crops on Mars.

00:43:33.920 --> 00:43:37.100 align:middle line:84%
We'll learn how to make not
only fuel and oxygen, which

00:43:37.100 --> 00:43:39.110 align:middle line:84%
is part of my own
Mars Direct plan,

00:43:39.110 --> 00:43:44.630 align:middle line:84%
but plastics, growing
food, of course,

00:43:44.630 --> 00:43:46.384 align:middle line:84%
fabrics, metals,
plastics, wires--

00:43:46.384 --> 00:43:48.050 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It will be
a mini planet Earth.

00:43:48.050 --> 00:43:49.850 align:middle line:84%
>>ZUBRIN: --tubes,
habitation structures.

00:43:49.850 --> 00:43:50.892 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Just like Earth.

00:43:50.892 --> 00:43:52.808 align:middle line:84%
>>ZUBRIN: Well, it'll
be different from Earth,

00:43:52.808 --> 00:43:54.650 align:middle line:84%
but it will be like
Earth in the place

00:43:54.650 --> 00:43:58.310 align:middle line:84%
that it will be
full of resources

00:43:58.310 --> 00:44:03.840 align:middle line:84%
that we have created by
inventing the technology

00:44:03.840 --> 00:44:06.900 align:middle line:90%
to bring them into being.

